From: bianbu-ci <bianbu-ci@spacemit.com>
Date: Fri, 18 Jul 2025 09:31:59 +0800
Subject: SpacemiT K1 RISC-V patches for GRUB 2.14

Four functional changes for SpacemiT K1 / Milk-V Jupiter RISC-V hardware:

1. EFI variable command (efivariable module) — read/export EFI variables
   from GRUB, supporting global and SpacemiT vendor GUIDs.

2. Block coalescing in filesystem reads — merge consecutive disk blocks
   into single grub_disk_read() calls to reduce I/O overhead on K1.

3. Firmware DTB bootargs merging — append GRUB kernel command line to
   firmware-provided /chosen/bootargs instead of replacing them.

4. RISC-V 64-bit EFI memory limit — restrict allocations to 4GB to
   avoid relocation overflows on multi-range memory layouts.

